        "node": {
          "id": 98704,
          "name": {
            "first": "Keiko",
            "last": "Tobe",
            "native": "戸部けいこ"
          },
          "language": "JAPANESE",
          "image": {
            "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/staff/large/3704.jpg",
            "medium": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/staff/medium/3704.jpg"
          },
          "description": "When she was in second grade, she made her first manga \"The Three Ghosts\". It was about three ghosts with different personalities having slapstick adventures in their owner's mansion. She then decided to be a mangaka. Her older brother also wanted to be a mangaka and he submitted all his manga artwork to Garo before shifting to oil painting and passing down his tools to her.\nAfter graduating, she married and had two sons. When her younger son was in kindergarten, he had a male classmate with autism. Later, she met the autistic boy's mother who said she wanted him to be a 'cheerful working adult'. This inspired Tobe to create \"With the Light,\" a manga dealing with autistic children. At that time, there were very few manga about disabilities and they never received attention. \"With the Light\" changed perspectives on this issue.",
          "siteUrl": "https://anilist.co/staff/98704"
